ABOUT IT !


USAGE:

- download relevant solar irridiation data for your location from http://rredc.nrel.gov/solar/new_data/India/
  (if you are in India; data might be available for other locations as well). 

- use the command 'tar -zxvf datafile' to unpack the data

- adjust the python script for your pump parameters and water conditions
(see details in the script file about the various parameters)

- standard pump data: for a 3x3 inch Agnimotors prototype employed in Bihar

- run the script with the according .csv file name as a parameter and it will output the amount
of water pumped for each of the 12 month in the according year (in a linux
shell: './solar_pump_calc.py datafile_2010.csv > 2010.txt' uses the csv file
as an input and saves the results in 2010.txt.


DATA

One Data set (source: NREL, see http://rredc.nrel.gov/solar/new_data/India/
for conditions of use) was included for a region in BIHAR and the year 2011.
Full data sets are provided by NREL.


